<div type="translation">
<head>Translation</head>
<p>For Aphrodite and for the gods the Augusti and for the People, Artemidoros Pedisas son of Dionysios, by birth of Artemidoros the son of Diogenes. at his own expense set up the Hermes, and the gilded Aphrodite, and the Erotes carrying torches on either side, and the marble Eros in front of it, as he also promised when the <seg cert="low">palm grove</seg> was being constructed in the period of his tenure of the office of strategos.</p>
</div>
<div type="commentary">
<head>Commentary</head>
<p>For a another dedication of Erotes, cf <xref type="inscription" n="1479" href="150202">15.202</xref>.</p>
</div>
<div type="history" n="locations">
